techmeme.title: Palo Alto Networks reports Q3 revenue up 15% YoY to $2.29B, vs. $2.28B est., net income down 6% to $262.1M, and non-GAAP gross margin of 76%, vs. 77.2% est. (Jonathan Vanian/CNBC)
Take-Two plans to sell $1B of new stock to investors and use the proceeds for general corporate purposes, including repayment of debt and future acquisitions (Jason Schreier/Bloomberg)
Google commits up to $150M, including $75M for product development and commercialization, as part of its partnership with Warby Parker to make smart glasses (Samantha Subin/CNBC)
Google launches SynthID Detector, a verification portal that lets users upload files and tries to identify if they contain content made with Google AI (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Xreal unveils Project Aura, expected to be the first Android XR glasses, powered by a separate puck with a Qualcomm chip, slated to launch by early 2026 (Mark Gurman/Bloomberg)
